        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 5:01PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mertzon, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mertzon, Sherwood, and Us-67 Near The Irion-Tom Green County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
